cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a novel method for text-to-image generation using a generative adversarial network. The focus is on controlling the image generation process based on natural language descriptions, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a word-level discriminator and attention-driven generator, which involve natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which could fall under computer graphics (cs.GR) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
